         <abstract>
            <p>A chain of nearly doubled primes is an ordered set $\{a_1, a_2,\ldots, a_\lambda\}$ of prime numbers, interlinked by $a_k = 2a_{k - 1} \pm 1$. A search for long chains of this kind has been performed in the range $a_1 &lt; 2^{50}$. Chains of length up to 13 have been found. Shorter chains have been counted in some restricted ranges. Some of these counts are compared with the frequencies predicted by a quantitative version of the prime $k$-tuples conjecture.</p>
          </abstract>
